<br>
&quot;Otaku&quot; was, long ago in feudal / samurai days, the word for &quot;you&quot;.  Think of it as being roughly equivalent to the word &quot;thou&quot;, as in the Ten Commandments' &quot;Thou shalt not steal&quot;.<br>
<br>
And... Yes, the next step was a group of comic-magazine nerds, addicted to the Japanese version of &quot;Conan the Barbarian&quot;/&quot;Prince-Valiant&quot;-type comicbooks.  These guys got DEEP into the whole culture, sort of like the American Dungeons&amp;Dragons guys who like to dress the part while playing the board-game, and like to be referred-to by their favorite RPG characters' names.  <br>
These guys started talking to each other in Medieval-Japanese style language... the equivalent of a Dungeons and Dragons guy talking to his buddies and saying &quot;Methinks thou art a sh*thead&quot; , or &quot;Will thee not give me a ride in thy steel-horse wagon ?&quot;<br>
<br>
These guys were enjoying a subculture alot like RenFest (Rennaissance Festival) or &quot;Society for Creative Anachronisms&quot;, minus the dressing-up in period costumes.<br>
<br>
Naturally, this opened them up to a bit of typecasting.  People started referring to them as &quot;Otaku&quot;, sort of like you could refer to a Southwestern American as a &quot;Y'all-er&quot; or Bronx kids as the kids who say &quot;badda-bing, badda-boom, fahgeddaboudit&quot;.<br>
<br>
It's worth noting that &quot;Otaku&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>DOES</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mean &quot;your house&quot;, in the same way that &quot;uchi&quot; in modern Japanese means &quot;me&quot;  and &quot;my home&quot;.  Try to think of it as being roughly equivalent to the medieval English practice of referring to &quot;the House of Atriedes&quot; (for example) as both the Atriedes family and their castle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=1193.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=1193.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=1193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.threadControl?topicID=1193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0